  "body": "## Abstract\r\nUpgrade for the current [eip-725](https://github.com/ethereum/EIPs/blob/master/EIPS/eip-725.md) .\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\n@frozeman  , @CJ42 and I  found that the better way to setData in `ERC725Y` is by passing an array of data which can be set in one transaction, that way we can skip the need to to make a contract call each time we want to set singular form of data.  Same applies for getData.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\n\r\n#### setData\r\n\r\nSets array of data at multiple keys. \r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction setData(bytes32[] calldata _keys, bytes[] calldata _values) public \r\n```\r\n\r\n#### getData\r\n\r\nReturns array of data at multiple keys.\r\n\r\n```solidity\r\nfunction getData(bytes32[] calldata _keys) public view returns(bytes[] memory)\r\n```",
