    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "i understand the point of view, but in my opinion, you can still use the standard interfaces of ERC725 and implement a batch function in your implementation contract to call the standard single function several times if needed, in terms of gas cost it is also better to do it this way as you don't want to call the batch function when you do a single add. \r\nAlso it would be a breaking change in the interfaces if you want to update the standard to this version, and would mean that the contracts already deployed would not be compatible with the new ABI, imo it is definitely a good idea but needs to be an addition to the implementation instead of a change in the standard interface itself ",
